# Testing And Coverage

- Logic-bearing code must have tests.
- The repository coverage target is 100% for `indoeuropop`.
- Prefer focused tests while iterating, then run the full gate before handing
  off substantial code changes:

  ```bash
  uv run pytest --cov=indoeuropop --cov-report=term-missing --cov-fail-under=100
  uv run black --check .
  uv run ruff check .
  uv run mypy src tests
  ```

- For small documentation/config-only changes, run targeted structural checks
  instead of pretending Python tests prove the docs.
- Test public behavior, error branches, malformed inputs, and generated
  artifact serialization.
- Do not lower thresholds, change coverage include/exclude settings, or mark
  real logic as ignored.
- If a full gate cannot be run, state exactly what was run and why the full gate
  was skipped.
